<subSubSection pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,438,1582]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1485,1510]" pageId="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
Mines of 
<taxonomicName authority="Monteiro &amp; Esposito, 2017" authorityName="Monteiro &amp; Esposito" authorityYear="2017" box="[428,633,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dryas" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[428,633,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4">Calycomyza dryas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[639,728,1485,1510]" pageId="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[639,728,1485,1510]" pageId="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are similar to mines of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" box="[991,1329,1485,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidis">
<emphasis box="[991,1224,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4">Calycomyza hyptidis</emphasis>
, Spencer
</taxonomicName>
, however this species can be distinguished by the mesophallus with a posterior digitiform projection basally and the distiphallus that is fused in the basal half.
</paragraph>
